# Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) API Test - AI Captone Project

## 📋 Overview

This is a beginner-friendly learning project for testing and building with *Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)* - Google's notification and messaging service.

*What You'll Learn:*
- ✅ How to set up Firebase project and authentication
- ✅ How to send notifications via FCM API
- ✅ Error handling and troubleshooting
- ✅ Best practices for notification delivery
- ✅ API testing and integration

*Project Status:* ✅ Beginner Learning Project  
*Language:* Python 3.8+  
*Last Updated:* March 2026

---

##  Quick Start (5 Minutes)

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.8 or higher
- Google account (for Firebase)
- VS Code or any code editor
- Internet connection

### Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone this repository
git clone https://github.com/AnneLeinaStep/fcm-notification-api-test.git
cd fcm-notification-api-test

# 2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# 3. Activate virtual environment
# On Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate
# On macOS/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

# 4. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 5. Set up Firebase credentials
# See SETUP.md for detailed instructions

# 6. Run the minimal example
python src/fcm_minimal_example.py
